message: Adding relevant pics to the article
Adding relevant and necessary pictures. No previous edits have been reverted in this one.
Identifying edits by El Greco as non constructive and reverting to previous edit by Jaetor06 (new photos are essential).
I didn't reshuffle the images El Greco (sorry, I mean Future Perfect...), new and more quality images were also added in order to improve the image of the article....when will you get this at last??
El Greco, please compare the article of Athens with the articles of THE REST of the European capitals. By comparison, we (because of you) have the fewest and the poorest pics. This adds no quality...
Adding necessary imagery on the article.
Adding necassary images on segments of the article and replacing old with new ones.
Reverting last edit by El Greco, identified as vandalism, to the previous one by Jaetor06.
Adding necessary imagery on the article
Putting back helpful images and correcting the Omonoia Square tag
/* Urban Landscape */ Correting  "Vasssileos Konstantinou Avenue", which is in Pangrati, to Aghiou Konstantinou Street.
This article contains less photos than most articles about major global cities do. Again, there are not so many photos here as for anyone to say that the article is a photo repository.
Added necessary image on history section. Replaced Lycabettus image with better one. Source (for El Greco): Wikipedia.
The article needs the replacement of some pictures to better and more representative ones, as is the case for the articles of ALL major global cities. Again, only one photo was added.
Only one new photo was added in the history section. A few others were simply changed to better and more representative ones so as the reader gets a better grasp of how Athens looks like today.
/* Suburbs */ Replaced photo with a more clear one.
/* Landmarks */ Replacing the previous picture of the Temple of Zeus etc.
/* Geography */ Changed the picture of Corfu to a far more beautiful one...
/* Demographics */ I liked this picture too, guys, alot in fact! Is this a better place to put it? I think it is! If not, do you propose another position?
The pictures format made by the previous user turned the page into a mess...
/* Urban Landscape */ This image of Athens can be properly placed here as it depicts an Athenian neighbourhood, Ambelokipi. I agree, too, that the other picture (kifissias ave) should be ommitted..
The new pics were accepted by everyone else but you El Greco (as it seems is always the case) so I'm really sorry if you don't like them but the pics of modern Athens are here to stay...
El Greco. having a few pics of modern Athens in the page does not render it a tourist guide! Why does this seem so difficult for you to comprehend anyway?
Replacement of the Athens Elefterios Venizelos Int'l Airport interior pic with a picture of the exterior of the building (Departures Level).
Replacement of the awkward map of the periphery of Athens with this intreresting view of Ambelokipi...
Reverted the image_skyline (Parthenon close-up). A broader view is much better...
